            <h2>Reflexology</h2>
            <p>Reflexology is an ancient practice originating from Egypt, India, and China and made its way to the west in the early 1900s. It aims to bring about a state of relaxation and help the body's own healing process. The main theory behind reflexology is that all the systems and organs of the body are mapped or reflected in smaller peripheral areas such as on the zones of the feet, the hands, ears and face. By working these areas and applying gentle pressure the aim is to restore balance facilitating the body's natural ability to optimise health and well-being. This treatment is also very effective in promoting deep relaxation and reducing stress.</p>
            <p><a href="https://www.aor.org.uk/" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">Association for reflexology</span><span class="icon aor"></span></a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
