            <h2>Reiki</h2>
            <p>“Reiki” is Japanese for 'universal life energy.'' This tradition was founded by Mikao Usui in the early 20th century and is an energy healing technique that promotes relaxation, reduces stress and anxiety through gentle touch. Treatment is given by placing hands gently on different areas of your body holding each position as energy flows. The hand positions are non-intrusive and are sometimes varied to allow Reiki energy to flow to areas where it is specifically needed. You may feel sensations such as heat, cold, tingling, see colours, feel emotional or you may feel very little. There is no right or wrong way to experience Reiki. Many people experience a sense of well-being and relaxation, some people even fall asleep. You take what you need from it, the practitioner simply is a channel for the energy to flow through. Most people feel very relaxed and at peace after a Reiki treatment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="eft" class="container">
        <div class="container-header reverse">
          <div class="copy">
            <h2>EFT</h2>
            <p>Emotional Freedom Technique is a meridian based therapy that draws on the traditional chinese medicine practice of acupuncture (without the needles). It is sometimes referred to as 'energy psychology' as it has both a psychological and an energetic component. It involves tapping key acupressure points on the hands, face, and body with your fingertips while focusing on and verbalising an uncomfortable emotion, belief or concerns, at the same time using positive affirmations to help to neutralise those feelings. Lightly tapping these points helps to move energy around the system and rebalances any disruption in energy flow. This process reduces stress and anxiety, increases mind body awareness and encourages cognitive shifts. EFT can be applied to anxieties, fears, phobias, anger, low self-esteem, PTSD, relationship issues, painful memories and much more.</p>
            <p><a href="https://eftinternational.org/" target="_blank"><span class="sr-only">EFT international</span><span class="icon eft"></span></a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="indheadmassage" class="container">
