            <h2>Indian Head Massage</h2>
            <p>Indian Head Massage is a relaxing treatment that focuses on massaging acupressure points on the head, neck and shoulders. These areas are often prone to stress and tension. The treatment is based on the ayurvedic system of healing and and has been practised in India for thousands of years. The practice was brought to England in the 1970's by Narendra Mehta who travelled to the West to study physiotherapy and was disappointed to see that massage did not include the head which he knew from personal experience has great benefits. He returned to India to study this in more detail and on his return began to teach the techniques and benefits of Indian Head Massage.</p>
            <p>Traditionally this treatment is done seated, but I find it more relaxing to lie down particularly if this is then followed by another treatment. Oil is applied to the hair but this can be also be done without the use of oil.</p>
            <p>The primary aim of Indian Head Massage is to promote good health and general well-being and it may help relieve stress and reduce tension. It may also ease migraine or headache pain, lower blood pressure, improve circulation to your head and neck, and promote hair growth.</p>
          </div>
